Using actuarial statistical analysis and modelling based upon Microsoft solutions, insurance companies are able to better identify risks, price¬policies more effectively, understand their liabilities more accurately,¬and optimise their financial positions.

As the pace of global financial services accelerates and speed becomes essential to decision-making, traditional tools are simply too slow. Coupled with massive on-premises server farms being unsustainably expensive, there is a real need for higher computing throughput but with a compelling TCO.

Microsoft analytics solutions enable financial institutions to benefit from cloud computing by reducing capex and facilitating more complex data analysis. Typical scenarios include risk computation and modelling plus predictive analytics through machine learning of data analysis & patterns.

Faced with exponentially increasing volumes of data, it is challenging for financial institutions to translate that data into insight needed to improve customer profitability and retention. To do this effectively, you need deeper insight into the profitability of you customer portfolio and have the ability to visualise that data so it is actionable.

With Microsoft customer and product analytics solutions, you can capitalise on internal and external data to combine profitability, segmentation and customer preference, to gain a complete end-to-end view of the customer.

The frequency of customer interactions with CSPs are increasing. As a result, mining greater volumes and a larger variety of data will become a powerful competitive asset. Microsoft big data solutions help with customer segmentation and analysis of customer loyalty and sentiment.

Sentiment analytics can be used to gauge customer satisfaction, allowing the service provider to proactively reach out to dissatisfied users, thus increasing customer loyally and reducing churn. Data streaming approaches with technologies like StreamInsight can dramatically improve fraud detection by analysing near real-time data windows without the need for long term storage.

Pattern matching and network telemetry can help pinpoint troublesome issues with network quality of customer equipment, allowing the operator to react more rapidly to potential problems—and thus improving overall quality of service and customer satisfaction.

Microsoft contact centre solutions improve the quality of the customer experience across all channels, drastically reducing the time needed to service sales and customer support contacts. Our solutions support a multitude of customer-facing experiences across social media, chat, and email; enable a back-end service desk; and offer incident management, skills-based routing, time-sensitive alerts, and customisable workflows.

Ease of workflow creation and management lowers the average call handling time. A rich set of APIs and plugins provides compatibility with third-party applications. The stability of the Microsoft platform keeps the solution always up and running.

Metrics and analytics provide better management of staffing and creating competitive call centre environments. The intuitive user interface is easy to learn for new agents, lowering time to on-board new staff, and integration with email, SharePoint, and spreadsheet applications reduce the number of windows and clicks required to service customers. Dashboards give agents graphical insight into how they are doing.
Tools and workflows help you monitor and manage collections and credit limits on accounts, as well as monitoring credits or chargebacks given to customers.

Rich campaign management features enable you to complete fast, targeted campaigns as well as measure effectiveness. Rich offer management lets you recommend services and products to customers based on their needs during acquisition and retention calls.
